article.headline: Eastern Wash. 94, Idaho State 87
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- Freshman Rodney Stuckey scored 29 points and grabbed six rebounds as Eastern Washington defeated Idaho State 94-87 Monday night. Neither team opened up more than a six-point lead in the first half. Eastern Washington (14-14, 9-5 Big Sky) started out hot, hitting seven of its first 10 shots and taking an early 18-12 lead on a basket by Deuce Smith at the 14:37 mark. Seniors Tim Henry and David Schroeder kept Idaho State (13-14, 4-10) in the game, combining for 29 of the team's first 31 points. The Bengals used a combination of tenacious man and zone defenses to slow Eastern Washington, and ended the half with a 7-0 run to grab a 45-41 halftime lead. Eastern Washington scored the first six points of the second half. From there, the teams battled back and forth. A basket by Kasey Winters gave Idaho State a 77-76 lead with 4:20 left, but it would prove to be the Bengals' last. Stuckey took the game over from there, scoring 11 of the Eagles' last 18 points as they closed the game with an 18-9 run. Idaho State's Henry finished the game with a career-high 35 points and Schroeder tied his career high, scoring 29. Paul Butorac and Rhett Humphrey each added 15 points for Eastern Washington.
